descript.abstract: This dataset represents geologic fault lines for a limited area along the Wasatch Front in Utah.
descript.purpose: For analysis and display at 1:24,000 scale. The data were digitized as part of State of Utah Comprehensive Emergency Earthquake Preparedness Program, 1986-1989.
descript.supplinf: Procedures_Used: Paper source maps were provided by CEM with hand-drawn corrections of certain faults. AGRC digitized the data using ARC/INFO. Attributes were read from the maps and coded manually. Reviews_Applied_to_Data: Hardcopy plots were overlaid on source maps and checked visually. Notes: This metadata document contains a composite of information for all tiles in the library.

attracc.attraccr: Feature attributes were taken from source material. Code assignment are believed to be representative of the source document.

dataqual.logic: Chain-node topology present. Data was reviewed for correct topological structure.
dataqual.complete: Data extend through only 21 quads in Weber, Davis, Salt Lake, and Utah Counties within the state of Utah.

horizpa.horizpar: Most data sources met NMAS standards for 1:24,000.
